title: For Sale:  5.7x28mm Federal American Eagle AE5728A TMJ 40 Grain; 1000 rounds
postcontent:
Selling 1,000 rounds of boxed, unopened, untouched Federal American Eagle AE5728A TMJ 40 Grain 5.7x28mm that I never got to shoot due to military deployments. 500 rounds are still in the manufacturer's cardboard brick-box that contains 10 boxes of 50 rounds each, and the other 500 are in their 50-round boxes. I am willing to sell at 500 round quantities.


Today (8/5/13) I sold my FN Five-seveN to a very lucky father and son, through an online listing. Unfortunately they were not able to also purchase the ammunition. I am returning to school to finish my engineering degree and could use the money for tuition and books.


The Federal American Eagle AE5728A Total Metal Jacket (TMJ) 5.7x28mm round is a Full Metal Jacketed (FMJ) 40 grain projectile that completely encases the lead core of the bullet with a very thick full copper jacket.  AE5728A rounds have muzzle velocity of 1,900 ft/s and muzzle energy of 324 ft-lb out of a FN P90.


These TMJ rounds will penetrate low level body armor even with the FN Five-seveN pistol, unlike the FNH 5.7mm SS197SR Blue Polymer Tip rounds which do not penetrate as well and are designed to fragment upon impact. There are other more penetrating rounds in the market but they are either very expensive, very rare, and/or illegal to own without being Law Enforcement or a government agency. American Eagle's 5.7mm TMJ rounds are currently LEGAL to purchase in the State of Florida and are the most cost effective 5.7mm round if you are looking for that type of performance or for high volume training.


These rounds are compatible with the FN Five-seveN, P90, PS90, the AR-57, and any other 5.7x28mm chambered firearms.


For any questions, or if interested, please contact me at REDACTED. Leave a message or text me if I do not answer immediately and I will get back to you as soon as I can. You can also contact me via email at REDACTED.
